com.qmetry.qaf.automation.data

Class BaseFormDataBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qmetry.qaf.automation.data.BaseDataBean
      • com.qmetry.qaf.automation.data.BaseFormDataBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataBean, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class BaseFormDataBean
extends BaseDataBean
    Base class to create FormDatabean which is kind of Data-bean specifically design to interact with UI forms. You can map bean properties with UI form fields by providing UiElement annotation with property and fill/fetch data to/from UI form.
    Author:
    Chirag Jayswal.
    See Also:
    UiElement

      • fillUiElements

        public void fillUiElements(java.lang.String... fieldLocs)
        it will fill up UI form fields given in argument with the property value one by one in order provided by UiElement.order(). If no argument if provided then it will fill all fields except read-only. To provide property specific custom implementation create filler method just like setter with Object as argument. For example if bean property is " String foo" then the filler method would be fillFoo(){}.
        Parameters:
        fieldLocs - optional field locators
        See Also:
        UiElement
